citation: REBIPP. 2021. List of Plant-Pollinator Interactions terms. Brazilian Network on Plant-Pollinator Interactions (REBIPP). http://rs.rebipp.org.br/ppi/doc/list/2021-12-03
creator: REBIPP
abstract: Plant-Pollinator Interactions (PPI) is a vocabulary standard for transmitting information about biological interactions between plants and animals. This document lists all terms in namespaces currently used in the vocabulary.

citation: REBIPP. 2021. Plant-Pollinator Interactions RDF Guide. Brazilian Network on Plant-Pollinator Interactions (REBIPP). http://rs.rebipp.org.br/ppi/terms/guides/rdf/
creator: REBIPP
abstract: This guide is intended to facilitate the use of Plant-Pollinator Interactions terms in the Resource Description Framework (RDF). It explains basic features of RDF and provides details of how to expose data in the form of RDF using Plant-Pollinator Interactions terms and terms from other key vocabularies. It defines terms in the namespace http://rs.rebipp.org.br/ppi/iri/ which are intended for use excusively with non-literal objects.
